==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: -ment
<hw>-ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[F. <ets>-ment</ets>, L.
<ets>-mentum</ets>.]</ety> <def>A suffix denoting <sig>that which
does</sig> a thing; <sig>an act</sig> or <sig>process</sig>; <sig>the
result of an act</sig> or <sig>process</sig>; <sig>state</sig> or
<sig>condition</sig>; <as>as, ali<ex>ment</ex>, that which nourishes,
orna<ex>ment</ex>, incre<ex>ment</ex>; frag<ex>ment</ex>, piece broken,
seg<ex>ment</ex>; abridg<ex>ment</ex>, act of abridging,
imprison<ex>ment</ex>, move<ex>ment</ex>, adjourn<ex>ment</ex>;
amaze<ex>ment</ex>, state of being amazed,
astonish<ex>ment</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ment</ent>⟦br⟧

